        "subject": "LU-19929 build: Add RISC-V to SUBARCH mapping",
        "message": "LU-19929 build: Add RISC-V to SUBARCH mapping\n\nAdd RISC-V architecture support (riscv64) to the SUBARCH\nmapping in build configuration. This refactors the existing\nsed-based approach to use case statements for better code\norganization and maintainability.\n\nThe SUBARCH variable is used throughout the build system to\ndetermine architecture-specific kernel paths and settings.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Abdul Halim <abdul.halim@openchip.com>\nChange-Id: I859e80f66e3ca2d8972f20a5ca7be0b6a52260cf\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64473\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
